description: Lists tracker resources in your Amazon Web Services account.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: An optional limit for the number of resources returned in a single call. Default value: 100

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The pagination token specifying which page of results to return in the response. If no token is provided, the default page is the first page. Default value: null.

nested_items.name: Entries
nested_items.description: Contains tracker resources in your Amazon Web Services account. Details include tracker name, description and timestamps for when the tracker was created and last updated.

nested_items.name: TrackerName
nested_items.description: The name of the tracker resource.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description for the tracker resource.

nested_items.name: PricingPlanDataSource
nested_items.description: No longer used. Always returns an empty string.

nested_items.name: CreateTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp for when the tracker resource was created in ISO 8601 format: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ.

nested_items.name: UpdateTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp at which the device's position was determined. Uses ISO 8601 format: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: A pagination token indicating there are additional pages available. You can use the token in a following request to fetch the next set of results.
